<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=alisonchacha&buddyTimeStamp=20050509&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fprocess_buddy.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193059697&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>AlisonChaCha</b>, our citizen of the week! <br><br>AlisonChaCha lives at <a href='/home/?user=alisonchacha'>3028 Willow Wood Way</a>, in the quaint old neighborhood of Ravenwood.  She moved to Millsberry on October 23, 2004, and her fellow citizens are already quite fond of her.<br><br>This fondness may be partially due to AlisonChaCha's charming nature.  Even those who have met her only once or twice are completely charmed by her engaging and witty conversation.  A common topic of discussion for AlisonChaCha is astronomy, one of her favorite subjects both inside and outside of school.  She loves anything related to the skies and space, which is why AlisonChaCha has spent many an afternoon in the Millsberry Arcade earning the shiny gold Galactic Defender Adventure trophy now featured in her home!<br><br>AlisonChaCha's fascination with the heavens goes far beyond games at the Millsberry Arcade or even books in the Millsberry Academy Library.  Vacation weekends often find her high among the clouds, enjoying one of her favorite hobbies: skydiving!  Once her feet are firmly on the ground, though, AlisonChaCha is also a top-flight athletic competitor, as her trophies from Sink the Three, Home Run Derby, and Rope Race prove.  <br><br>Despite her numerous accomplishments, AlisonChaCha remains very modest. That's why her friends are always comfortable hanging out with her at the pool, her tree house, or their favorite shops around Downtown Millsberry.  If you ask her friends what kind of clothes AlisonChaCha shops for, they'll tell you that she likes to keep things simple, sporting either black and white, or light blue - the color of the sky.<br><br>Besides astronomy, AlisonChaCha's other great passion is dancing.  In fact, the nickname "ChaCha" comes from her agile ability to perform that tricky ballroom dance.  Her CD player usually contains some catchy polka, disco, or salsa music.  Just hit the play button and check out her fancy moves!<br><br>AlisonChaCha's dancing isn't the only movement that she's involved in, though.  She is also a very dedicated member of the movement to make Millsberry the very best community it can be!  You can often find her at Peabody Park, swaying to the sound of her favorite tunes on her headphones while helping to keep trash off the grass.  She also recently made a rather large donation to the Millsberry Community Center's Building Fund, which was vital to completing the Community Center's construction.<br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, AlisonChaCha, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
